@startuml CarrySprintDFDLevel1

title CarrySprint Data Flow Diagram (Level 1)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

actor "User" as user
rectangle "Web Browser" as browser
rectangle "P1 Web Gateway Process" as p1
rectangle "P2 Application Process" as p2
database "System SQLite\nsystem.sqlite" as db_system
database "Project SQLite\nproject_<id>.sqlite" as db_project

user --> browser : Open top page\nSelect project\nEdit task\nApply carry-over\nSet menu visibility
browser --> p1 : HTTP JSON request
p1 --> p2 : ZeroMQ JSON command
p2 --> db_system : SQL read/write
p2 --> db_project : SQL read/write

db_system --> p2 : rowset/result
db_project --> p2 : rowset/result
p2 --> p1 : ZeroMQ JSON response
p1 --> browser : HTTP JSON response
browser --> user : top-page menu buttons\nbudget-in/budget-out\nresource/calendar\nerror message

note right of p1
  P1 validates route and payload.
  P1 never accesses SQLite.
end note

note right of p2
  P2 executes domain logic.
  P2 controls transaction boundary.
end note

note bottom of db_system
  users, user_menu_visibility,
  startup admin bootstrap data.
end note

note bottom of db_project
  sprint and planning data.
end note

@enduml
